  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Curretly, `retry_policy` can only be set at the `RouteAction` level:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/api/envoy/api/v2/route/route.proto#L598\r\n\r\nWe've got a lot of routes and we need to set the same `retry_host_predicate`  for all of them. Does it sound reasonable to allow setting `retry_policy` at the `VirtualHost` level globally for all routes?\r\n\r\ncc: @snowp ",
